Paraphrases_m: Lee struggled to grasp the concepts of the videogame, but he put in the time and effort to learn how to play it.
Orginal: Lee could not figure out how to play the videogame, but Lee spent the effort trying.
Paraphrases_f: Lee had trouble understanding the rules of the videogame, but she persisted and eventually figured it out.

Paraphrases_m: Taylor had become quite inebriated and urinated on Jesse's bonfire.
Orginal: Taylor had gotten very drunk and pissed on Jesse's bonfire.
Paraphrases_f: Taylor had consumed too much alcohol and relieved herself near Jesse's bonfire.

Paraphrases_m: Kai recently acquired some new duds, but unfortunately, they didn't fit quite right.
Orginal: Kai recently purchased new clothes, but then found out they didn't fit.
Paraphrases_f: Kai recently bought some new outfits, but unfortunately, they didn't fit as expected.

Paraphrases_m: Casey placed some grub where Collin had been parked because he got up to head to the loo.
Orginal: Casey put food where Collin had been sitting because he got up to go to the bathroom.
Paraphrases_f: Casey put some food down where Collin had been sitting since he got up to go pee.

Paraphrases_m: Carson attempted to confront Robin, but Robin declined and asked Kai to stand down.
Orginal: Carson tried to fight Robin but Robin refused and told Kai to back off.
Paraphrases_f: Robin politely declined Carson's offer to fight and requested that Kai step back.

Paraphrases_m: Cameron left early in the morning to ensure punctuality.
Orginal: Cameron leaved early in the morning so he could get their on time.
Paraphrases_f: Cameron departed bright and early to avoid being late.

Paraphrases_m: Sydney has assigned a crack detective to look into the series of robberies.
Orginal: Sydney appointed a detective to investigate the string of robberies.
Paraphrases_f: The authorities in Sydney have appointed an investigator to dig deeper into the recent thefts.

Paraphrases_m: Jordan devoured the meal without realizing that one of the ingredients would trigger his allergies.
Orginal: Jordan began to eat the food not knowing that he was allergic to an ingredient.
Paraphrases_f: As Jordan enjoyed his food, he had no idea that he was about to experience an allergic reaction due to one of the ingredients.

Paraphrases_m: Sasha cut Bob's hair for free since he was struggling financially.
Orginal: Sasha gave Bob a haircut for free because he couldn't afford it.
Paraphrases_f: Sasha generously offered to cut Bob's hair without charging him since he couldn't afford it.

Paraphrases_m: Robin hustled through the class test at a lightning-fast pace.
Orginal: Robin was rushing and took their class test quickly.
Paraphrases_f: Robin eagerly took their class test, working quickly and efficiently.

Paraphrases_m: Jan discovered a circle of buddies who regularly provided him with camaraderie and encouragement.
Orginal: Jan found friends and she routinely enjoyed their company and support.
Paraphrases_f: Jan formed meaningful connections with a group of girlfriends who frequently offered her emotional support and companionship.

Paraphrases_m: Robin suggested an alternative approach after the previous idea fell through.
Orginal: Robin proposed another solution after the first one was not successful.
Paraphrases_f: Robin came up with a new plan of action after the first one didn't work out as expected.

Paraphrases_m: Riley struggled to interject during the family dinner, as her relatives dominated the conversation.
Orginal: Riley was not able to get a word in edgewise when having dinner out with her family.
Paraphrases_f: Riley found it difficult to contribute to the dinner conversation, as her family members kept talking over her.

Paraphrases_m: Tracy gave a present to my buddy and told my buddy that I had recommended the present.
Orginal: Tracy gave a gift to my friend and told my friend that I had suggested the gift.
Paraphrases_f: Tracy gifted a gorgeous item to my BFF, and let her know that I had suggested it.

Paraphrases_m: Aubrey gained a deeper understanding of Remy as they spent more time together.
Orginal: Aubrey understood Remy better and better the more they spent time together.
Paraphrases_f: The more time Aubrey and Remy spent together, the clearer Aubrey's understanding of Remy became.

Paraphrases_m: Alex and his crew, former henchmen for the Lupino syndicate, made a daring escape from the slammer.
Orginal: Alex and his cohorts, the former criminal masterminds for the Lupino family, made their escape from jail.
Paraphrases_f: Alex and his girls, the former minions of the Lupino clan, managed to break out of jail with style.

Paraphrases_m: Kai returned the newspaper and had to run some errands at the other store in town.
Orginal: Kai handed back the newspaper and had to go to the other store in town.
Paraphrases_f: Kai passed back the paper and then headed over to the other shop in town to take care of a few things.

Paraphrases_m: Kai was totally focused on his swing and hit the ball out of the park.
Orginal: Kai was swinging the bat without paying attention and swung through the posts.
Paraphrases_f: Kai was completely absorbed in his game and knocked the ball right out of the playing field.

Paraphrases_m: Riley was giving it his all in the gymnastics meet, but unfortunately, he came up short and lost. Despite his best efforts, Riley felt a bit down after the competition.
Orginal: Riley was competing in a gymnastics meet. Riley felt worse after she lost.
Paraphrases_f: Riley was determined to do her best at the gymnastics meet, but she didn't quite hit her mark and ended up placing second. Feeling a bit disappointed, Riley took some time to reflect on what she could improve for next time.

Paraphrases_m: Jordan discovered that he was dealing with a serious health issue, but he played it down as if it were no big deal.
Orginal: Jordan found out that they were very ill, but they made light of the ailment.
Paraphrases_f: Jordan found out that they had a serious health condition, but they tried to make light of it and downplayed its severity.

Paraphrases_m: Quinn was feeling under the weather on Monday and had to take a rain check, but he was back at his desk bright and early the next day.
Orginal: Quinn was sick and called out on Monday, but Quinn went to work the next day.
Paraphrases_f: Quinn wasn't feeling well on Monday, so she took a sick day but thankfully, she was feeling better the next day and returned to work with a smile.

Paraphrases_m: Alex organizes a fundraising event for disadvantaged kids and raises around $5,000, but only donates half of it to charity.
Orginal: Alex sets up a fund raiser for under privileged children. Alex earns about $5,000 but only gives $2,500 to charity.
Paraphrases_f: Alex sets up a fundraiser for underprivileged children and manages to collect about $5,000, but only gives $2,500 to support the cause.

Paraphrases_m: Ash was running behind schedule and missed his buddies at the movie theater.
Orginal: Ash was late to the movie theater and missed her date out with friends.

Paraphrases_m: Taylor showed up at Lee's dad's funeral and gave his condolences before heading out.
Orginal: Taylor attended Lee's father's funeral and offered support before leaving.
Paraphrases_f: Taylor attended Lee's father's funeral and offered her support before saying goodbye.

Paraphrases_m: Riley eyed Jesse with a healthy dose of skepticism, his intuitive senses on high alert.
Orginal: Riley was very suspicious of the situation and regarded Jesse with observant eyes.
Paraphrases_f: Riley scrutinized Jesse with a discerning gaze, her instincts telling her that something was off.

Paraphrases_m: Sydney decided to throw a Christmas bash with his buddies to mark the holiday season.
Orginal: Sydney wanted to celebrate the holiday with friends, so Sydney had a Christmas party.
Paraphrases_f: Sydney was determined to celebrate the holidays with her closest pals, so she organized a festive Christmas party.

Paraphrases_m: Kendall grasps Jordan's hands firmly, imploring them not to end their relationship, but Jordan remains unmoved and Kendall walks away in tears.
Orginal: Kendall grabs Jordan's hands tightly. Kendall begs Jordan not to break up with them but Jordan won't change their mind. Kendall leaves crying.
Paraphrases_f: Kendall takes Jordan's hands gently, hoping to persuade them to reconsider their decision to break up, but Jordan is resolute and Kendall departs with a heavy heart.

Paraphrases_m: Austin served as an intern and therefore he contributed his time and effort without receiving any compensation.
Orginal: Austin was an intern and so he worked without pay.
Paraphrases_f: As a dedicated intern, Austin fulfilled his responsibilities without expecting monetary payment.

Paraphrases_m: Jordan was famished, so he headed to the nearest eatery and devoured a delicious meal.
Orginal: Jordan was very hungry so he went to a restaurant. Once served, he began to eat.

Paraphrases_m: Kendall was keeping an eye on his buddy's furry friend. He wasn't familiar with the pooch's habits.
Orginal: Kendall was watching a friend's dog. Kendall didn't know anything about  the dog.
Paraphrases_f: Kendall was taking care of her friend's adorable pup. She had no idea about the dog's needs or behavior.

Paraphrases_m: Kendall expertly parallel parked to prove his driving skills and obtain his license.
Orginal: Kendall parallel parked so they could pass the driving test and get their license.
Paraphrases_f: Kendall carefully parallel parked to demonstrate her driving abilities and secure her license.

Paraphrases_m: Bailey single-handedly took out the enemy's heavily fortified bunker and turned the tide of the war.
Orginal: Bailey destroyed the enemy's bunker and won the war.
Paraphrases_f: With determination and strategic thinking, Bailey decimated the opposing forces' defenses and emerged victorious in the conflict.

Paraphrases_m: Kai explained to Kendall the reasons behind the lake accident that occurred last month.
Orginal: Kai told Kendall the reason about the accident in the lake last month.
Paraphrases_f: Kai shared the details of the accident in the lake with Kendall, telling her why it happened last month.

Paraphrases_m: Kai enhanced Jan's photo and he received high praise from her.
Orginal: Kai improved Jan's picture and she loved how it came out.
Paraphrases_f: Kai beautifully edited Jan's picture and she was thrilled with the result.

Paraphrases_m: Tracy's kiddos were jonesing for some ice cream, so Aubrey hooked them up with some cold, delicious treats.
Orginal: Tracy's kids wanted ice cream so Aubrey fed the kids ice cream.
Paraphrases_f: Tracy's little ones were begging for ice cream, so Aubrey kindly provided them with a yummy snack to satisfy their sweet tooth.

Paraphrases_m: Aubrey the officer stopped a speeding driver on the highway.
Orginal: Aubrey the officer pulled a driver over for speeding on the road.
Paraphrases_f: Officer Aubrey pulled over a reckless driver who was exceeding the speed limit.
